# Azure AI Compliance Evidence Checklist

This checklist guides the analyst in capturing compliance evidence for the use of Azure AI Foundry, GPT models, and Embedding models.  
Each screenshot must include visible browser metadata (URL bar, date/time in footer).  
Save each file with the exact filename specified below.

---

## Checklist of Screenshots (with URLs)

- [ ] **01_AzureAI_PrivacyStatement.png** – Azure AI Foundry Privacy Statement page (Microsoft data privacy commitments).  
  URL: [https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/privacystatement](https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/privacystatement)

- [ ] **02_AzureAI_ResponsibleAI.png** – Responsible AI principles page (Microsoft Responsible AI compliance).  
  URL: [https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/ai/responsible-ai](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/ai/responsible-ai)

- [ ] **03_OpenAI_DataPrivacy.png** – Azure OpenAI Service data, privacy, and security documentation.  
  URL: [https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/legal/cognitive-services/openai/data-privacy](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/legal/cognitive-services/openai/data-privacy)

- [ ] **04_DataRetention_Policy.png** – Data retention policy for Azure OpenAI / LLMs.  
  URL: [https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/legal/cognitive-services/openai/data-privacy#how-long-is-customer-data-retained](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/legal/cognitive-services/openai/data-privacy#how-long-is-customer-data-retained)

- [ ] **05_PCI_PII_Exclusion.png** – Azure compliance documentation on exclusion of PCI/PII/financial data.  
  URL: [https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/compliance/offerings/](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/compliance/offerings/)

- [ ] **06_EncryptionAtRest.png** – Encryption at rest and in transit – Microsoft Trust Center.  
  URL: [https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/security/fundamentals/encryption-overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/security/fundamentals/encryption-overview)

- [ ] **07_Compliance_Certifications.png** – Azure compliance offerings (SOC 2, ISO, GDPR).  
  URL: [https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/compliance/](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/compliance/)

- [ ] **08_ModelDataUsage.png** – Azure OpenAI FAQ confirming no customer data is used for training.  
  URL: [https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/legal/cognitive-services/openai/data-privacy#is-customer-data-used-to-train-microsofts-models](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/legal/cognitive-services/openai/data-privacy#is-customer-data-used-to-train-microsofts-models)

- [ ] **09_Data_Controls.png** – Azure Policy / Key Vault integration for governance controls.  
  URL: [https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/key-vault/general/overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/key-vault/general/overview)

---

## Browser Metadata Requirements

- Capture full URL in the browser address bar.  
- Ensure system date/time is visible in the screenshot footer.  
- Use Chrome or Edge in full-screen mode.  
- Do not crop out metadata.

---

## Additional Evidence

In addition to screenshots, the following evidence must be collected:

- SOC 2 Type II Report for Azure OpenAI (request via Microsoft Compliance portal: [https://servicetrust.microsoft.com/](https://servicetrust.microsoft.com/))  
- Written declaration from Microsoft’s CEO, CTO, or equivalent authoritative figure confirming data privacy posture.
